item.title: Pamela Anderson: Beauty is Power (Encore)
item.description: Just in time for Thanksgiving, we bring you a celebrity we’re truly thankful for. Pamela’s early life is plagued by violence and she’s afraid she’ll never get out of Canada – until a chance spot on a Jumbotron launches her into the public eye – and straight to the Playboy Mansion. item.title: SOPP707: I started with a piece which was marked to be played articulated legato, and I had no idea what it was about
item.description:
Let’s start episode 707 of Secrets of Organ Playing Podcast. This question was sent by Fanie.  And she writes: Dear Vidas, I am an adult beginner, so I have different needs.
1. What is your dream for organ playing? To play chorales in the church and play music which I love, like Bach, Buxtehude, Bohm, Franck, Mendelssohn, Guilmant, Vierne, Widor etc.
2. What are 3 most important things that are holding you back from realizing your dream? I am not sure... Feed: https://anchor.fm/s/9b0909c/podcast/rss
